 in charges and convictions in the Black population. This exploration of the complex and often contradictory web of racial attitudes and the values of white legal elites not only exposes how blackness was articulated in Canadian law but also offers a rare glimpse of black life as experienced in Canada's past.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBlacksxLegal status, laws, etcxHistoryxOntario. 0aBlacksxLegal status, laws, etc.xHistoryxOntario. 0aBlacksxSocial conditionsxOntario. 0aDiscrimination dans l'administration de la justice pénalexHistoirexOntario. 0aDiscrimination in criminal justice administrationxHistoryxOntario. 0aDiscrimination racialexHistoirexOntarioxOntario. 0aNoirsxConditions socialesxOntario. 0aNoirsxDroitxHistoirexOntario. 0aRace discriminationxHistoryxOntario. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311049095440uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266722840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442667228423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442667228.jpg  a978-3-11-049095-4  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK